'''西城調車場'''（{{lang-en|'''West Side Yard'''}}），正式名稱為'''約翰·D·凱米爾西城調車場'''（{{lang|en|'''John D. Caemmerer West Side Yard'''}}），是位於[[美國|美國]][[紐約|紐約]][[曼哈頓|曼哈頓]]{{Link-en|曼哈頓西城|West Side (Manhattan)|西城}}的[[車輛段|列車基地]]，由[[紐約大都會運輸署|紐約大都會運輸署]]擁有，功能是儲放[[長島鐵路|長島鐵路]]的[[通勤列車|通勤列車]]，佔地約 {{convert|26.17|acres|ha}}，由北邊的西33街、南側的西30街，東邊的[[第十大道|第十大道]]及西邊的{{Link-en|第十二大道 (曼哈頓)|Twelfth Avenue (Manhattan)|第十二大道}}所圍，內有數條儲車軌、6條簡易維修軌、一座長約12節列車的清潔用[[月台|月台]]，還有供鐵道職員使用的休息室和更衣間<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtawsy.com/en-US/ |title=West Side Rail Yard (Request for Proposals for Development) |work=Metropolitan Transportation Authority |date=2007-07-13 |accessdate=2010-03-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323145842/http://www.mtawsy.com/en-US |archivedate=2010-03-23 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mta.info/mta/investor/pdf/2004_annual_report.pdf |title=2004 Annual Report |format=PDF |publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority |page=66 |accessdate=2010-03-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090313203853/http://mta.info/mta/investor/pdf/2004_annual_report.pdf |archivedate=2009-03-13 }}</ref>。西城調車場曾被一條沿著曼哈頓西部興建的-{zh-hans:架空; zh-hk:架空; zh-tw:高架;}-貨運支線作為北方端點，如今該鐵道已被改建成稱作「[[紐約高架公園|紐約高架公園]]」的空中綠色走廊，調車場隔壁街區則是[[賈維茨會展中心|賈維茨會展中心]]。

西城調車場的全稱以已故[[紐約州參議院|紐約州參議員]]{{Link-en|約翰·D·凱米爾|John D. Caemmerer}}命名，這位出身自{{Link-en|東威利斯頓 (紐約州)|East Williston, New York|東威利斯頓}}的律師兼政治家曾捐贈1億9,570美元的建設經費，使該調車場得以興建<ref>{{cite news |title=The Air Above Rail Yards Still Free |first=Mary |last=Voboril |newspaper=Newsday |location=New York |date=March 26, 2005}}</ref>。

==歷史==
西城調車場原址是一座[[哈德遜河鐵路|哈德遜河鐵路]]的維修廠，替其沿著{{link-en|第十一大道 (曼哈頓)|Eleventh Avenue (Manhattan)|第十一大道}}行走的一條鐵路線提供支援，當時的法令基於安全考量，不允許列車駛入23街以南地帶。之後[[紐約中央鐵路|紐約中央鐵路]]及其後的[[賓州中央交通公司|賓州中央鐵路]]都著手擴建了這座鐵路基地，一直到1970年代以前都作為[[貨運列車|貨運列車]]的終點使用<ref name="newsday-2005-03-26"/>。

當西城調車場在1987年啟用之後，長島鐵路於早晨[[繁忙時間|尖峰時段]]開抵西端終點站——[[紐約賓州車站|紐約賓州車站]]的列車不再需要像從前一樣，清客並空車返回[[長島_(紐約州)|長島]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Far West Side Story |first=Matthew |last=Doherty |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/11/07/nyregion/07tunn.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=November 7, 2004 |accessdate=2010-03-06 |archive-date=2015-05-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528034202/http://www.nytimes.com/2004/11/07/nyregion/07tunn.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="newsday-2005-03-26">{{cite news |title=The Air Above Rail Yards Still Free |first=Mary |last=Voboril |newspaper=Newsday |location=New York |date=March 26, 2005}}</ref>，而得以利用該調車場調度，進而增加了長島鐵路在賓州車站的尖峰載客能力<ref>{{cite news |title=Problems Halt Laying of Pipe at L.I.R.R. Project |first=Ralph |last=Blumenthal |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1984/02/21/nyregion/problems-halt-laying-of-pipe-at-lirr-project.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=February 21, 1984 |accessdate=2010-03-05 |archive-date=2020-04-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422050645/https://www.nytimes.com/1984/02/21/nyregion/problems-halt-laying-of-pipe-at-lirr-project.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。西城調車場興建期間，同時施作了一條地下隧道，賓州車站發出的[[美鐵|美鐵]]列車於1991年4月7日起開始，能利用該隧道駛入{{Link-en|西城線 (紐約中央鐵路)|West Side Line (NYCRR)|西城線}}、前往[[紐約上州|紐約上州]]<ref name="newsday-2005-03-26"/>。在此之前，美鐵的{{Link-en|帝國服務列車|Empire Service (Amtrak)}}都是從曼哈頓東部的[[大中央車站|大中央車站]]發車<ref>{{cite news |title=Travel Advisory; Grand Central Trains Rerouted To Penn Station |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1991/04/07/travel/travel-advisory-grand-central-trains-rerouted-to-penn-station.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=April 7, 1991 |accessdate=2010-03-06 |archive-date=2021-02-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211214054/https://www.nytimes.com/1991/04/07/travel/travel-advisory-grand-central-trains-rerouted-to-penn-station.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

目前西城調車場的上蓋為2012年動工的[[哈德逊城市广场|哈德逊城市广场]]都市開發計畫的主要用地。調車場建設之時，其結構設計考量到{{Link-en|上空權|air rights}}，以便在未來發展[[上蓋開發|上蓋物業]]；軌道之間也預留了空間，可以安插月台增設時所需的梁柱<ref name="newsday-2005-03-26"/>。[[麥迪遜廣場花園|麥迪遜廣場花園]]在1980年代中期曾打算選擇西城調車場的用地作為館址，接著也成為[[紐約洋基隊|紐約洋基隊]]新球場的可能設置地<ref>{{cite news |title=Owners of Garden Said to Weight Building New Arena Further West |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1985/12/28/nyregion/owners-of-garden-said-to-weight-building-new-arena-farther-west.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=December 28, 1985 |accessdate=2010-03-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Mayor Making Case for Yanks on West Side |first=Dan |last=Barry |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1998/04/20/nyregion/mayor-making-case-for-yanks-on-west-side.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=April 20, 1998 |accessdate=2010-03-06 |archive-date=2020-04-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422050702/https://www.nytimes.com/1998/04/20/nyregion/mayor-making-case-for-yanks-on-west-side.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。之後，政府預定將調車場打造成一座大型的運動場建築群，當中包括替[[紐約噴射機|紐約噴射機球隊]]和{{link-en|紐約申辦2012年夏季奧運會計劃|New York City bid for the 2012 Summer Olympics|申辦2012年夏季奧運}}而興建的{{Link-en|西城體育館|West Side Stadium}}<ref>{{cite news |title=Giuliani Offers Plan to Put Up Sports Complex |first=Dan |last=Barry |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1999/01/15/nyregion/giuliani-offers-plan-to-put-up-sports-complex.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=January 15, 1999 |accessdate=2010-03-06 |archive-date=2018-06-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615190859/https://www.nytimes.com/1999/01/15/nyregion/giuliani-offers-plan-to-put-up-sports-complex.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=From Ashes of Olympic Bid, a Future Rises for the Far West Side |first=Charles V. |last=Bagli |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/11/28/nyregion/on-far-west-side-bloombergs-failed-olympic-plan-spurs-development.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=November 27, 2011 |accessdate=2011-11-28 |archive-date=2021-03-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210314032312/http://www.nytimes.com/2011/11/28/nyregion/on-far-west-side-bloombergs-failed-olympic-plan-spurs-development.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2005年1月，西城調車場的東半場（十一大道以東）在「[[哈德遜城市廣場_(物業)|哈德遜城市廣場]]」計畫中被定為住宅用地；之後隨著西城體育館的興建計畫宣告失敗，因此西半場在2009年12月時劃分為住宅與商業發展區<ref>{{cite news |title=What Rises in the West? Uncertainty |first=Joyce |last=Purnick |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2005/01/20/nyregion/20matters.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=January 20, 2005 |accessdate=2010-03-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Rezoning Will Allow Railyard Project to Advance |first=Charles V. |last=Bagli |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/12/22/nyregion/22hudson.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=December 21, 2009 |accessdate=2010-03-06 |archive-date=2021-05-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210508113705/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/12/22/nyregion/22hudson.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

